default3.2 
default              
defaultIn Greater 
defaultManchester
default we have sought to harness central and local funds in new ways to support our growth priorities for many years. We have developed an Investment Fund that has allowed us to coordinate funds to deliver growth priorities across the city region with an emphasi
defaults on recyclable investment. We have also worked with government to develop the innovat
defaultive 
defaultEarnback
default Model which allows
default us to capture a proportion of the growth generated as a result of our local investment in transport infrastructure for reinvestment. 
defaultThis 
defaultis based on a formula
default linked to changes in 
defaultrateable values over time at the Greater Manchester level, which provides a revenue stream over 30 years
default, provided that
default additional GVA is created relative to the agreed baseline. 
defaultThis therefore provides an additio
defaultnal incentive for Greater Manchester to prioritise local government spending to maximise 
defaulteconomic
default growth. 
default&#xa0;
default3.3
default              
defaultWe want to build on these approaches to drive long term growth through using new financial models that support early investment
default f
defaultor projects whe
defaultre 
